<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14096">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Farm%20Mechanics.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-1432">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1432 mb-requirement-id-1433">
        (a) Discuss with your counselor the safety equipment, tools, and
        clothing used while checking or repairing farm equipment. Use this
        equipment, tools, and/or clothing (when needed or called for) in meeting
        the requirements for this merit badge. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/cT0xTWFjDsY" target="_blank"
          >Farm Equipment Dangers —Staying Safe Around Farm Machinery (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.growerexperts.com/ppe-in-agriculture/"
          target="_blank"
          >The Comprehensive Guide to PPE for Farmers: Safety From Head to Toe
          (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/9rjaXpUKPqI" target="_blank"
          >Safety on the Farm: General Safety (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/lRYxf9giLQI" target="_blank"
          >Working Safely With Hand Tools Around the Farm (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Yjl1rqqjosU" target="_blank"
          >Personal Protective Equipment in the Farm (PPE) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1432 mb-requirement-id-1434">
        (b) Draw a plan showing a well-equipped farm shop. Point out the shop's
        mandatory safety devices and features. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLfmcXlkwVLVWPdGbiJMiCM3jdJF304pTq"
          target="_blank"
          >Playlist of Top Shops (playlist)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/turaJrzpgcg" target="_blank"
          >Farmer's Dream Shop Features Rolling Carts, In-Floor Tie Downs | Top
          Shops® | Successful Farming (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Bss30MpMqLA" target="_blank"
          >The Largest Farm Shop We've Ever Seen | Top Shops® | Successful
          Farming (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1432 mb-requirement-id-1435">
        (c) Find all the universal warning and safety symbols on a piece of
        equipment and explain what they mean. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/x50qcaHzNy8" target="_blank"
          >Caterpillar Warning Symbols/Icons Detailed Guide (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.scribd.com/document/889441066/Graphical-Symbols-for-Operator-Controls-and-Displays-on-Agricultural-Equipment"
          target="_blank"
          >Agricultural Equipment Symbol Standards (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1432 mb-requirement-id-1436">
        (d) Describe what a safety data sheet (SDS) is and tell why it is used.
        Obtain the SDS for any engine coolant, oil, grease, fuel, hydraulic or
        transmission fluid, or other flammable or hazardous materials you use in
        meeting the requirements for this merit badge. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/_yWF-w3CwmU" target="_blank"
          >Safety Data Sheets (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.hseblog.com/where-find-sds/" target="_blank"
          >Where to Find Safety Data Sheets (SDS): A Complete Guide (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-1437">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Explain how power is produced or transferred in a:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1437 mb-requirement-id-1438">
        (a) Diesel engine <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/qeGQgPQsJJI" target="_blank"
          >How a Diesel Engine Works (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/8ruuieWiXT4" target="_blank"
          >How Diesel Engine Actually Works? (Animation) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1437 mb-requirement-id-1439">
        (b) Hydraulic system <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/52IMMQSB9Hs" target="_blank"
          >How Does a Hydraulic Cylinder Work? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1437 mb-requirement-id-1440">
        (c) Transmission or any other power system <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zJuhem5LuAg" target="_blank"
          >Tractor Transmission System: Common Methods (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-1441">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1441 mb-requirement-id-1442">
        (a) Replace the handle of any tool found on the farm. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/CPmkVm9CYkw" target="_blank"
          >How To Replace a Garden Tool Handle (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/g0aC6xOppio" target="_blank"
          >Axe &amp; Hammer Handle Replacement—How To Do It Old School
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1441 mb-requirement-id-1443">
        (b) Organize a tool rack or a storage system for nails, bolts, nuts, and
        washers. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/twlFjHccSfE" target="_blank"
          >Adam Savage's Hardware Logjam Sorting Challenge! (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/ja3olvly0Ic" target="_blank"
          >Easy Bolt Sorter (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/7OSkChtwlJA" target="_blank"
          >How To Organise Screws, Nails, Bolts &amp; Nuts (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/pAP2m90RLhA" target="_blank"
          >How To Organize Your Loose Screws and Nails (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1441 mb-requirement-id-1444">
        (c) Using a hand file, properly dress the mushroomed head of a chisel or
        punch. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/1xiIuBbH1SQ" target="_blank"
          >4 Tools You Can Use To Dress a Chisel (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Q5wyhqKtnqo" target="_blank"
          >Dressing Hammers and Punches—Basic Blacksmithing (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1441 mb-requirement-id-1445">
        (d) Using a hand file, correctly dress a screwdriver tip. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.tiktok.com/@paul.a.j.sellers/video/6854554012323171590"
          target="_blank"
          >Sharpening and Reshaping Your Screwdriver With a File (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-1446">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1446 mb-requirement-id-1447">
        (a) On an engine-powered machine: Grease all fittings, change the oil
        and oil filter, clean the air filter, clean the radiator fins, and
        replace the fuel filters. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/2HhdyfFzjWI" target="_blank"
          >Do This Every Two Weeks and Your Tractor Will Never Break Down
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1446 mb-requirement-id-1448">
        (b) For any engine-powered machine, create a preoperational checklist;
        include checking the engine coolant, engine oil, hydraulic and/or
        transmission fluid, and battery voltage (using a voltmeter). Using your
        checklist, conduct a preoperational check of that machinery or
        equipment. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.worksafebc.com/en/resources/health-safety/checklist/equipment-and-machine-safety-checklist"
          target="_blank"
          >Download Equipment and Machine Safety Checklist (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1446 mb-requirement-id-1449">
        (c) Prepare any farm machine for winter storage. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rjwAwPDBrqk" target="_blank"
          >Winterizing Your Tractor and Equipment: 10 Essential Steps (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.tiktok.com/@michiganmarinefarmer/video/7596082158477921566"
          target="_blank"
          >Preparing the Combine for Winter Storage (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-1450">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Visit an implement dealer. Interview the dealer technician or service
      manager for hints on good preventive maintenance. Ask why it is important,
      the costs, and what causes wear or damage. Report what you learn.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-1451">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Explain each step in ONE of the following maintenance procedures:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1451 mb-requirement-id-1452">
        (a) Tightening hydraulic fittings. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://cntopa.com/avoid-leaks-how-to-tighten-hydraulic-fittings-the-right-way.html"
          target="_blank"
          >Avoid Leaks! How To Tighten Hydraulic Fittings the Right Way
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1451 mb-requirement-id-1453">
        (b) Checking the air filter. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/571Oz9LrBwk" target="_blank"
          >Maintaining Your Tractor—Changing the Air Filter (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-1451 mb-requirement-id-1454">
        (c) Cleaning a work piece with a wire-brush wheel. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/wPR2Lbmn7wM" target="_blank"
          >Cleaning Up Rusted Metal Finds (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-1455">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Find out about three career opportunities in farm mechanics. Pick one and
      find out the education, training, and experience required for this
      profession. Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this
      profession might interest you. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/J7s3lBNr6VI" target="_blank"
        >Agricultural Engineering (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/lYkXBAc6Elk" target="_blank"
        >Agriculture Careers: Agriculture Equipment Technician (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/KEuPYD1gcXw" target="_blank"
        >Careers in Agriculture—Management (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/o3mov6oKoUI" target="_blank"
        >Careers in Agriculture—Technology (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/7B9V96I5Rxs" target="_blank"
        >Agricultural Equipment Technician (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
